1
00:02:31,400 --> 00:02:32,600
PREVIOUS EPISODE

2
00:02:32,680 --> 00:02:36,160
This is Uncle Tharin's amulet.
I want you to wear it,

3
00:02:36,760 --> 00:02:37,960
so you'll be safe.

4
00:02:38,560 --> 00:02:39,440
Teacher.

5
00:02:40,160 --> 00:02:41,640
This song is…

6
00:02:41,720 --> 00:02:43,160
"Soft Heart" lyrics.

7
00:02:43,240 --> 00:02:45,200
It's the song you used to sing for me.

8
00:02:45,840 --> 00:02:47,640
It is a song full of memories.

9
00:02:47,720 --> 00:02:50,240
I wrote it for a man

10
00:02:51,400 --> 00:02:53,120
who I loved most in my life.

11
00:02:53,200 --> 00:02:56,120
Come and record it tomorrow.

12
00:02:56,680 --> 00:02:58,000
This song

13
00:02:58,520 --> 00:03:01,400
will be your debut.

14
00:03:01,480 --> 00:03:05,040
Bai Tong Music
is promoting Puna's new song.

15
00:03:05,120 --> 00:03:07,480
Look, the views are skyrocketing!

16
00:03:07,560 --> 00:03:08,520
That's right.

17
00:03:09,920 --> 00:03:10,640
Puna's moved

18
00:03:11,600 --> 00:03:13,240
to Boss Nok's label now.

19
00:03:13,320 --> 00:03:16,720
You just gave her to someone else
and let them snatch the opportunity.

20
00:03:16,800 --> 00:03:19,640
I think that's not right!
We've built her up for so long,

21
00:03:19,720 --> 00:03:20,920
and now you give her away?

22
00:03:43,640 --> 00:03:44,480
Yes, Dad?

23
00:03:45,880 --> 00:03:46,800
Sonrak.

24
00:03:47,600 --> 00:03:49,760
You're at Boos Nok's company, right?

25
00:03:49,840 --> 00:03:51,080
Yes, Dad.

26
00:03:51,160 --> 00:03:53,440
I want you to find a way
to get close to Puna

27
00:03:54,080 --> 00:03:56,200
and make sure she's yours.

28
00:03:57,080 --> 00:04:00,440
Huh? Why, Dad?

29
00:04:01,680 --> 00:04:03,520
I want you to grab her from head to toe,

30
00:04:03,600 --> 00:04:05,080
make her your wife.

31
00:04:05,600 --> 00:04:06,560
Can you do that?

32
00:04:07,320 --> 00:04:08,360
Dad, I…

33
00:04:08,880 --> 00:04:11,880
How could I do that?
I'm not close enough to her yet.

34
00:04:14,320 --> 00:04:17,360
I want you to use
your relationship with her

35
00:04:18,000 --> 00:04:20,040
to pull her back to our label.

36
00:04:21,720 --> 00:04:22,680
Whatever.

37
00:04:22,760 --> 00:04:24,240
Handle it this way for now.

38
00:04:25,240 --> 00:04:27,720
Leave the love stuff for later, okay?

39
00:04:32,040 --> 00:04:33,160
PARKING LOT

40
00:04:34,200 --> 00:04:36,280
-Puna's coming out. I'll go call her.
-No need.

41
00:04:38,720 --> 00:04:41,040
-Puna.
-Mr. Sonrak.

42
00:04:41,120 --> 00:04:44,960
Well, I wanted to invite you over
to my place

43
00:04:45,040 --> 00:04:46,960
to cook together. You're free, right?

44
00:04:54,200 --> 00:04:55,240
I'm free.

45
00:04:57,560 --> 00:04:58,760
That's perfect.

46
00:04:59,560 --> 00:05:01,880
But Teacher Mueangphrai has to come too.

47
00:05:01,960 --> 00:05:03,560
Of course, no problem.

48
00:05:03,640 --> 00:05:05,040
Let's go then.

49
00:05:09,080 --> 00:05:10,840
Wait, Teacher.

50
00:05:10,920 --> 00:05:12,520
What is it, Chaiya?

51
00:05:13,560 --> 00:05:16,120
Tell Puna to be careful.
Don't trust Sonrak.

52
00:05:16,200 --> 00:05:19,000
Got it. I'll handle it.

53
00:05:49,520 --> 00:05:53,640
Hey, Chaiya, you can wait in the car.
No need to come inside.

54
00:05:53,720 --> 00:05:54,600
Okay.

55
00:05:55,240 --> 00:05:57,200
But if you need help with the cooking,

56
00:05:57,920 --> 00:05:58,920
just call me.

57
00:06:00,920 --> 00:06:04,120
Let's go, Puna. Come inside. This way.

58
00:06:24,560 --> 00:06:26,160
Make sure you succeed, Sonrak.

59
00:06:30,080 --> 00:06:31,040
This way.

60
00:06:31,880 --> 00:06:32,920
Please have a seat.

61
00:06:38,040 --> 00:06:39,080
Have a seat.

62
00:06:41,880 --> 00:06:45,360
Puna, this is Chef Mark, my friend.
He runs his own restaurant.

63
00:06:45,440 --> 00:06:48,280
Today my dad asked him
to cook at the house,

64
00:06:48,360 --> 00:06:50,040
so I invited him

65
00:06:50,120 --> 00:06:52,360
to try your dishes.

66
00:06:53,320 --> 00:06:54,720
Puna's cooking is really amazing!

67
00:06:55,640 --> 00:06:58,720
I believe you,
but I have to head back quickly today.

68
00:06:58,800 --> 00:07:01,160
-What?
-Maybe next time.

69
00:07:02,040 --> 00:07:05,720
Okay. I'm really just a home cook.

70
00:07:05,800 --> 00:07:07,440
I'm not confident to show off my skills.

71
00:07:08,120 --> 00:07:11,440
That's what makes a home cook's touch
sharper than a professional chef's.

72
00:07:12,960 --> 00:07:14,720
What did you make today?

73
00:07:14,800 --> 00:07:16,680
Your dad ordered some appetizers.

74
00:07:16,760 --> 00:07:17,720
Want to try them first?

75
00:07:17,800 --> 00:07:19,600
I'm not very comfortable

76
00:07:19,680 --> 00:07:21,480
with Western dishes.

77
00:07:22,680 --> 00:07:25,600
I'll step outside for a walk.

78
00:07:25,680 --> 00:07:27,000
Let the young ones dig in.

79
00:07:30,880 --> 00:07:32,760
Let's start with the appetizers.

80
00:07:32,840 --> 00:07:35,160
Some bread with French butter

81
00:07:35,240 --> 00:07:36,680
and a bit of spinach.

82
00:07:41,200 --> 00:07:44,200
Oh, such tiny pieces. How cute!

83
00:07:45,000 --> 00:07:45,840
Come on.

84
00:07:45,920 --> 00:07:47,640
Let's taste it. I'll serve you.

85
00:07:55,400 --> 00:07:56,800
Let's try it.

86
00:07:58,040 --> 00:08:01,160
I'll let you show your skills later.
Cheers!

87
00:08:01,240 --> 00:08:02,200
Okay.

88
00:08:02,920 --> 00:08:03,880
Try it.

89
00:08:04,760 --> 00:08:06,120
Oh, wait!

90
00:08:07,000 --> 00:08:08,360
Before tasting,

91
00:08:09,440 --> 00:08:10,440
let me go live real quick.

92
00:08:12,120 --> 00:08:13,320
Just a sec.

93
00:08:13,400 --> 00:08:14,760
Hello everyone!

94
00:08:15,480 --> 00:08:16,520
Quick live update.

95
00:08:16,600 --> 00:08:20,080
Right now, I'm with Chef Mark and Puna.

96
00:08:20,160 --> 00:08:21,800
Today we're tasting

97
00:08:21,880 --> 00:08:24,840
Chef Mark's cooking to see how it is.

98
00:08:26,120 --> 00:08:27,440
Let's check it out!

99
00:08:31,640 --> 00:08:33,159
It's so good!

100
00:08:33,240 --> 00:08:36,799
I didn't expect such a small piece
to taste this amazing.

101
00:08:36,880 --> 00:08:37,919
Really?

102
00:08:39,440 --> 00:08:42,440
I'll get some cold drinks
to cleanse your palates.

103
00:08:58,680 --> 00:09:00,440
You're really enjoying it, Pincher Puna!

104
00:09:12,680 --> 00:09:13,640
Can I help you?

105
00:09:13,720 --> 00:09:15,240
Just came to get some water.

106
00:09:15,320 --> 00:09:17,560
Sure, the drinking water's in the fridge.

107
00:09:18,920 --> 00:09:20,920
-Wait!
-Yes?

108
00:09:21,000 --> 00:09:22,440
Are you going to serve them?

109
00:09:22,520 --> 00:09:24,440
-Yes.
-Oh.

110
00:09:24,520 --> 00:09:28,480
My niece doesn't like butterfly pea drink.

111
00:09:29,840 --> 00:09:32,880
Just one glass will do. Okay?

112
00:09:33,440 --> 00:09:34,280
Yes.

113
00:09:35,120 --> 00:09:36,680
-I'll go serve it now.
-Okay.

114
00:09:45,840 --> 00:09:47,600
-The drinks are ready.
-Everyone.

115
00:09:49,360 --> 00:09:53,360
We've finished the appetizers.
And now, to finish off,

116
00:09:53,960 --> 00:09:55,760
the butterfly pea drink.

117
00:09:58,640 --> 00:09:59,880
So refreshing.

118
00:10:01,720 --> 00:10:03,160
Looks like you're hungry.

119
00:10:03,240 --> 00:10:04,600
Of course!

120
00:10:06,000 --> 00:10:08,760
Everyone, next up,

121
00:10:09,440 --> 00:10:13,920
Puna will show her cooking skills.

122
00:10:14,000 --> 00:10:16,280
I'm lucky to taste it first.

123
00:10:16,880 --> 00:10:20,240
Then I'll cleanse my palate
with the butterfly pea drink.

124
00:10:20,320 --> 00:10:21,480
Bottom's up!

125
00:11:11,080 --> 00:11:13,720
Puna and Teacher Mueangphrai
are acting strangely.

126
00:11:15,600 --> 00:11:17,760
Do they know Sonrak's plan?

127
00:11:20,040 --> 00:11:21,160
What are they up to?

128
00:11:24,800 --> 00:11:27,160
Come on, Puna. This way, please.

129
00:11:30,560 --> 00:11:32,960
Everyone, from now on,

130
00:11:33,040 --> 00:11:37,080
we'll watch Puna cook for us!

131
00:11:38,000 --> 00:11:39,760
I'm shy after Chef Mark's cooking.

132
00:11:39,840 --> 00:11:41,720
No need to be shy. Chef Mark's gone.

133
00:11:42,240 --> 00:11:44,800
The kitchen is all yours now, Puna.

134
00:11:44,880 --> 00:11:48,480
Alright, I'll check the fridge first
to see what's inside.

135
00:11:48,560 --> 00:11:49,760
Sure, go ahead.

136
00:12:06,040 --> 00:12:07,040
Puna.

137
00:12:07,120 --> 00:12:09,440
Excuse me for a moment.

138
00:12:10,200 --> 00:12:11,040
Where are you going?

139
00:12:11,920 --> 00:12:12,800
To the bathroom.

140
00:12:14,120 --> 00:12:15,000
Okay.

141
00:12:15,600 --> 00:12:18,600
Everyone, I'm ending the live stream here.

142
00:12:19,160 --> 00:12:20,400
See you next time!

143
00:12:31,200 --> 00:12:32,320
Where's Sonrak?

144
00:12:32,400 --> 00:12:33,760
He went to the bathroom.

145
00:12:35,000 --> 00:12:36,160
The medicine worked, right?

146
00:12:37,040 --> 00:12:39,720
Yes, he left just now.

147
00:12:39,800 --> 00:12:42,000
Alright, let's split tasks.

148
00:12:42,080 --> 00:12:44,880
Teacher, can you cook
in the kitchen instead of Puna?

149
00:12:45,560 --> 00:12:47,840
Puna, go grab the doll upstairs.

150
00:12:48,440 --> 00:12:49,800
I'll monitor the situation.

151
00:12:49,880 --> 00:12:52,080
If anything seems off,
I'll call immediately.

152
00:12:52,760 --> 00:12:53,800
Puna.

153
00:12:54,560 --> 00:12:56,720
Mute your phone and set it to vibrate.

154
00:12:58,680 --> 00:13:00,480
Good plan.

155
00:13:00,560 --> 00:13:03,000
Truly like a real cop.

156
00:13:09,960 --> 00:13:11,880
Go, hurry!

157
00:13:11,960 --> 00:13:12,800
-Yes, Teacher.
-Go.

158
00:13:27,800 --> 00:13:31,080
Where's Mr. Sonrak's room?

159
00:13:36,600 --> 00:13:37,800
Maybe it's this one?

160
00:13:56,960 --> 00:13:58,760
If he comes in, I'm in trouble.

161
00:14:13,240 --> 00:14:14,400
Who's in the room?

162
00:14:21,680 --> 00:14:23,360
Sonrak must be with Puna.

163
00:14:23,920 --> 00:14:25,080
And they…

164
00:14:37,400 --> 00:14:39,320
This room's just like in that livestream.

165
00:14:42,040 --> 00:14:43,880
It has to be Mr. Sonrak's room.

166
00:14:45,600 --> 00:14:46,760
The bear!

167
00:14:51,080 --> 00:14:52,280
That bear's not here.

168
00:15:14,720 --> 00:15:16,040
Not in the closet either.

169
00:15:17,200 --> 00:15:18,760
It has to be somewhere in this room.

170
00:15:22,080 --> 00:15:23,000
Whoa.

171
00:15:24,600 --> 00:15:26,160
Singha's actually home?

172
00:15:32,320 --> 00:15:33,400
Chaiya.

173
00:15:34,320 --> 00:15:35,840
What are you doing here?

174
00:15:39,880 --> 00:15:43,240
Mr. Sonrak told me to watch the car.
I'm just following his order.

175
00:15:46,640 --> 00:15:47,720
Did you see Chef Mark?

176
00:15:49,360 --> 00:15:50,680
He went back already.

177
00:15:50,760 --> 00:15:52,360
He's already prepared the food for you.

178
00:15:52,960 --> 00:15:55,960
He said if you want to eat,
Aunt Riam can heat it up.

179
00:16:11,480 --> 00:16:12,720
And Aunt Riam?

180
00:16:16,000 --> 00:16:17,000
She went grocery shopping.

181
00:16:36,240 --> 00:16:38,640
Hey, Teacher. What are you doing here?

182
00:16:40,080 --> 00:16:42,400
I'm preparing food for Mr. Sonrak.

183
00:16:43,240 --> 00:16:47,560
He asked me and Puna to cook here.

184
00:16:47,640 --> 00:16:49,320
I see.

185
00:16:49,400 --> 00:16:51,880
So now, Sonrak and Puna are together?

186
00:16:56,600 --> 00:16:57,640
Dad.

187
00:16:57,720 --> 00:16:59,600
Hey, where have you been?

188
00:16:59,680 --> 00:17:02,720
I went to the bathroom.
My stomach wasn't feeling well.

189
00:17:02,800 --> 00:17:04,200
And Puna?

190
00:17:06,520 --> 00:17:08,079
Teacher, where's Puna?

191
00:17:08,160 --> 00:17:09,839
She just stepped out a moment ago.

192
00:17:10,440 --> 00:17:11,440
Probably went to the bathroom.

193
00:17:11,520 --> 00:17:12,520
I see.

194
00:17:12,599 --> 00:17:13,599
Went to the bathroom?

195
00:17:15,160 --> 00:17:16,599
There's only one downstairs.

196
00:17:16,680 --> 00:17:18,319
And Sonrak just came out.

197
00:17:19,359 --> 00:17:22,079
So where did Puna go?

198
00:17:25,280 --> 00:17:26,680
Maybe she went upstairs, Dad.

199
00:17:39,480 --> 00:17:40,320
Chaiya.

200
00:17:41,080 --> 00:17:43,880
Puna, Singha is downstairs.

201
00:17:43,960 --> 00:17:46,080
And Sonrak's just coming out
of the bathroom.

202
00:17:47,000 --> 00:17:48,960
Looks like they're about to go upstairs.

203
00:17:49,040 --> 00:17:51,040
What should I do? That's it for now.

204
00:17:54,800 --> 00:17:56,080
Oh no.

205
00:17:57,680 --> 00:17:58,800
Hey, Sonrak.

206
00:17:59,840 --> 00:18:03,160
I think Puna probably sneaked
into your room to use the bathroom.

207
00:18:04,000 --> 00:18:05,520
Is that so?

208
00:18:06,120 --> 00:18:09,800
Earlier, when I came down,
I saw your door just close.

209
00:18:09,880 --> 00:18:13,040
At first, I thought you were with Puna,
so I didn't interfere.

210
00:18:13,120 --> 00:18:16,960
Puna must have a bad stomach, Dad.

211
00:18:17,040 --> 00:18:18,480
Don't talk so much.

212
00:18:19,120 --> 00:18:20,360
Hurry upstairs

213
00:18:21,320 --> 00:18:24,320
and take care of it. Got it?

214
00:18:26,440 --> 00:18:27,600
Go!

215
00:18:28,600 --> 00:18:29,720
Go now!

216
00:18:34,320 --> 00:18:36,120
Hold on, Teacher.

217
00:18:36,200 --> 00:18:38,720
I saw you had some food prepared, right?

218
00:18:39,920 --> 00:18:42,560
Take me to eat it.
Let the kids chat over here.

219
00:18:43,360 --> 00:18:45,760
Come on. I'm hungry. Let's go.

220
00:18:45,840 --> 00:18:47,760
-Oh my.
-What did you prepare earlier?

221
00:18:48,360 --> 00:18:50,320
Seriously, he's gone upstairs.

222
00:18:52,960 --> 00:18:54,200
What should I do?

223
00:18:55,520 --> 00:18:57,400
Puna, you've got to get through this.

224
00:19:06,600 --> 00:19:07,600
Puna.

225
00:19:10,160 --> 00:19:13,120
Puna! Are you in here, Puna?

226
00:19:14,680 --> 00:19:17,960
-Puna.
-Well, Mr. Sonrak.

227
00:19:19,040 --> 00:19:21,760
I'm sorry for barging into your bathroom.

228
00:19:21,840 --> 00:19:25,560
I couldn't find the maid's restroom.

229
00:19:25,640 --> 00:19:27,080
No, it's fine.

230
00:19:27,960 --> 00:19:29,480
Did you have an upset stomach?

231
00:19:29,560 --> 00:19:32,080
Oh, yes. Not sure what I ate.

232
00:19:32,160 --> 00:19:33,720
Me too.

233
00:19:33,800 --> 00:19:36,320
Probably because of
Chef Mark's appetizers.

234
00:19:38,240 --> 00:19:39,640
Geez.

235
00:19:50,960 --> 00:19:52,080
Puna.

236
00:19:53,880 --> 00:19:55,280
Well…

237
00:19:59,040 --> 00:20:02,360
Oh! My stomach feels better now.

238
00:20:02,440 --> 00:20:05,560
Shall we go downstairs?

239
00:20:11,120 --> 00:20:12,160
Puna.

240
00:20:15,280 --> 00:20:16,920
I need to go.

241
00:20:18,880 --> 00:20:21,560
-Puna.
-Mr. Sonrak, what are you doing?

242
00:20:22,160 --> 00:20:24,040
I love you, Puna.

243
00:20:24,720 --> 00:20:26,680
Hey! Mr. Sonrak!

244
00:20:30,560 --> 00:20:31,720
What should I do?

245
00:20:32,880 --> 00:20:34,680
Sonrak's definitely up to something bad.

246
00:20:37,560 --> 00:20:39,320
I love you, Puna.

247
00:20:39,400 --> 00:20:40,480
I'm sorry.

248
00:20:41,840 --> 00:20:44,360
-Mr. Sonrak!
-I'm sorry, Puna. I love you.

249
00:20:49,000 --> 00:20:50,200
Puna!

250
00:20:51,280 --> 00:20:53,440
Puna!

251
00:20:55,920 --> 00:20:58,480
-The bear!
-Puna!

252
00:20:59,360 --> 00:21:01,640
-Puna! Open the door!
-Go away! Stay away from me!

253
00:21:03,280 --> 00:21:05,240
Puna, I didn't mean it! I'm sorry!

254
00:21:05,320 --> 00:21:07,440
Don't make excuses! Go away!

255
00:21:08,800 --> 00:21:10,240
Puna, open the door for me.

256
00:21:10,320 --> 00:21:11,480
I'm sorry. I'm begging you.

257
00:21:14,720 --> 00:21:15,920
Please open the door for me.

258
00:21:16,000 --> 00:21:18,000
I swear I didn't mean it.
I won't do this again.

259
00:21:18,080 --> 00:21:19,240
Stay away from me!

260
00:21:19,320 --> 00:21:21,400
I won't do it again. Puna, please.

261
00:21:21,480 --> 00:21:23,320
Go away!

262
00:21:23,400 --> 00:21:25,480
Puna, I didn't mean it. Please.

263
00:21:25,560 --> 00:21:27,840
I'll make sure this never happens again.
Puna, please.

264
00:21:27,920 --> 00:21:29,200
Puna, open up.

265
00:21:29,280 --> 00:21:31,400
-Chaiya.
-Puna!

266
00:21:32,040 --> 00:21:35,040
-I'm here to help.
-Puna, I'm begging you!

267
00:21:38,080 --> 00:21:39,560
You toss the teddy bear down first.

268
00:21:40,240 --> 00:21:42,640
Then climb down fast. Go now!

269
00:21:51,120 --> 00:21:53,640
Puna, open the door!

270
00:21:57,840 --> 00:21:59,120
Puna, open it!

271
00:21:59,200 --> 00:22:01,160
Open it, Puna!

272
00:22:03,800 --> 00:22:04,800
Puna.

273
00:22:06,240 --> 00:22:07,560
I'm begging you.

274
00:22:08,720 --> 00:22:09,960
Puna, please open.

275
00:22:11,640 --> 00:22:13,680
I won't let this happen again. I'm sorry.

276
00:22:13,760 --> 00:22:15,760
I beg you. I'm really sorry, Puna.

277
00:22:28,920 --> 00:22:30,840
Hurry! He's coming!

278
00:22:32,000 --> 00:22:33,240
Puna.

279
00:22:33,320 --> 00:22:35,840
Please, Puna. Open the door!

280
00:22:42,720 --> 00:22:43,680
Puna!

281
00:22:44,960 --> 00:22:46,520
-Puna!
-Hey!

282
00:22:48,520 --> 00:22:49,720
That's Mr. Sonrak's voice.

283
00:22:50,320 --> 00:22:53,040
Relax, Teacher. It's a matter
between the young couple.

284
00:22:57,160 --> 00:22:58,000
Puna!

285
00:22:59,280 --> 00:23:00,960
Puna, where are you?

286
00:23:01,040 --> 00:23:02,200
Puna!

287
00:23:03,240 --> 00:23:04,280
Puna!

288
00:23:15,760 --> 00:23:16,960
Puna, where are you?

289
00:23:18,280 --> 00:23:21,400
Whoa! Something's definitely happening!

290
00:23:25,880 --> 00:23:27,080
Puna!

291
00:23:28,320 --> 00:23:30,640
Sonrak, what's going on?

292
00:23:30,720 --> 00:23:33,880
Dad, I don't know where Puna went.

293
00:23:33,960 --> 00:23:36,120
She was just here a moment ago.

294
00:23:36,200 --> 00:23:38,760
Wait! What did you do to Puna, Mr. Sonrak?

295
00:23:38,840 --> 00:23:40,240
Why did she run off?

296
00:23:41,640 --> 00:23:43,240
Let's go downstairs and talk.

297
00:23:43,840 --> 00:23:44,840
Yes, Dad.

298
00:23:45,880 --> 00:23:46,840
Puna!

299
00:23:47,560 --> 00:23:50,800
Puna! Hey, where did you go?

300
00:24:01,720 --> 00:24:04,400
What happened? Did he do something to you?

301
00:24:05,000 --> 00:24:06,720
He tried to harass me.

302
00:24:06,800 --> 00:24:08,520
But I managed to escape to the balcony.

303
00:24:08,600 --> 00:24:10,720
Chaiya helped me, so I got away.

304
00:24:11,960 --> 00:24:13,800
The father and son are both terrible.

305
00:24:16,080 --> 00:24:17,880
Thank you so much, Chaiya.

306
00:24:18,640 --> 00:24:20,280
If it weren't for you, I'd be in trouble.

307
00:24:20,960 --> 00:24:22,320
Honestly,

308
00:24:22,960 --> 00:24:25,040
I didn't want you to risk going in there.

309
00:24:26,280 --> 00:24:27,360
But it's necessary.

310
00:24:28,600 --> 00:24:30,920
All the evidence is in that bear.

311
00:24:31,920 --> 00:24:33,760
I have to get it out.

312
00:24:36,360 --> 00:24:37,400
Wait.

313
00:24:38,040 --> 00:24:39,840
I threw the bear out.

314
00:24:39,920 --> 00:24:40,960
Where is it now?

315
00:24:45,600 --> 00:24:46,480
There it is.

316
00:24:47,040 --> 00:24:48,080
The bear is over there.

317
00:24:53,200 --> 00:24:54,320
Oh no.

318
00:24:54,840 --> 00:24:56,560
How am I going to get it now?

319
00:25:05,760 --> 00:25:07,240
Did you take care of Puna?

320
00:25:10,520 --> 00:25:13,440
No, she got away.

321
00:25:13,520 --> 00:25:14,520
Geez.

322
00:25:15,280 --> 00:25:16,760
You really are useless.

323
00:25:16,840 --> 00:25:19,080
Dad, I…

324
00:25:19,160 --> 00:25:21,160
I've never done anything like this before.

325
00:25:22,040 --> 00:25:23,200
The chance is gone.

326
00:25:23,760 --> 00:25:25,160
Don't even hope for another.

327
00:25:26,120 --> 00:25:27,720
Dad, Puna's here.

328
00:25:27,800 --> 00:25:28,920
Hey, come here.

329
00:25:29,000 --> 00:25:31,320
Chaiya, you have no right
to do this to her!

330
00:25:33,440 --> 00:25:36,200
I saw Puna escape
from Mr. Sonrak's balcony.

331
00:25:36,280 --> 00:25:37,800
She was acting strange,

332
00:25:37,880 --> 00:25:39,160
so I chased her down.

333
00:25:39,960 --> 00:25:43,000
I don't know if she stole anything
from Mr. Sonrak's room.

334
00:25:43,080 --> 00:25:45,160
I didn't steal anything, but I got…

335
00:25:45,240 --> 00:25:48,040
Got what? Hey, tell me.

336
00:25:48,120 --> 00:25:49,800
-Who hurt you?
-Puna wasn't hurt at all.

337
00:25:49,880 --> 00:25:52,200
-Who hurt you, Puna?
-Puna wasn't hurt at all.

338
00:25:53,760 --> 00:25:55,200
Today was just a misunderstanding.

339
00:25:55,760 --> 00:25:56,720
Right, Sonrak?

340
00:25:59,040 --> 00:26:01,440
Yes, it was a misunderstanding.

341
00:26:01,520 --> 00:26:06,160
Puna, I won't do anything
to upset you like this again.

342
00:26:07,400 --> 00:26:09,720
Then I'll take my leave.

343
00:26:14,640 --> 00:26:16,880
There must be more going on here.

344
00:26:16,960 --> 00:26:17,840
Teacher.

345
00:26:18,680 --> 00:26:20,800
Right now, Puna
is considered a new singer.

346
00:26:21,560 --> 00:26:23,240
All the media are watching.

347
00:26:24,240 --> 00:26:27,880
If today's incident
is talked about in the wrong way,

348
00:26:27,960 --> 00:26:29,280
it'll look bad.

349
00:26:30,600 --> 00:26:32,960
Think carefully before you say anything.

350
00:26:37,440 --> 00:26:38,400
Puna.

351
00:26:40,040 --> 00:26:43,560
Please, let's just end this here.

352
00:26:44,880 --> 00:26:47,480
I won't let something like this
happen again.

353
00:26:47,560 --> 00:26:48,600
Please, Puna.

354
00:27:01,320 --> 00:27:03,840
I'll accept whatever you want me to do.

355
00:27:03,920 --> 00:27:04,920
I'm sorry.

356
00:27:08,080 --> 00:27:09,160
Alright.

357
00:27:09,920 --> 00:27:11,200
That's settled. Get inside.

358
00:27:12,000 --> 00:27:14,520
You were preparing food, right?
Go handle it.

359
00:27:14,600 --> 00:27:17,440
No, I'm leaving. Excuse me.

360
00:27:17,520 --> 00:27:18,920
-I'll give you a ride.
-No need.

361
00:27:23,160 --> 00:27:24,120
Let's go, Teacher.

362
00:27:32,560 --> 00:27:34,680
Puna's gone. I'll lock the house.

363
00:27:35,320 --> 00:27:36,200
Go ahead.

364
00:27:38,280 --> 00:27:39,720
She's angry with me, Dad.

365
00:27:42,240 --> 00:27:44,000
Don't dwell on it.

366
00:27:44,080 --> 00:27:46,480
Go inside. We'll figure out another way.

367
00:28:00,720 --> 00:28:03,440
How did this teddy bear end up here?

368
00:28:04,480 --> 00:28:06,880
Well, Aunt…

369
00:28:06,960 --> 00:28:09,320
I'm Aunt Riam. I'm the housekeeper here.

370
00:28:09,400 --> 00:28:11,360
I just got back from running some errands.

371
00:28:11,440 --> 00:28:13,520
By the way,

372
00:28:14,120 --> 00:28:15,240
you're a guest

373
00:28:16,360 --> 00:28:17,560
of Mr. Sonrak, right?

374
00:28:18,400 --> 00:28:20,240
Oh, I remember now!

375
00:28:20,320 --> 00:28:21,880
You're Miss Puna,

376
00:28:21,960 --> 00:28:24,240
the singer of "Soft Heart",
aren't you? I remember you.

377
00:28:25,120 --> 00:28:26,760
Yes, that's me. I'm about to head back.

378
00:28:26,840 --> 00:28:27,880
I see.

379
00:28:28,720 --> 00:28:32,720
But this teddy bear, I had it drying

380
00:28:32,800 --> 00:28:34,880
on Mr. Sonrak's balcony.
How did it end up here?

381
00:28:36,240 --> 00:28:38,040
I'm not sure about that either.

382
00:28:39,680 --> 00:28:40,640
Auntie.

383
00:28:40,720 --> 00:28:43,520
Can I have this bear?

384
00:28:43,600 --> 00:28:46,000
I really like this bear so much.

385
00:28:46,080 --> 00:28:47,480
No, you can't.

386
00:28:47,560 --> 00:28:49,560
Mr. Singha really cherishes this one.

387
00:28:50,800 --> 00:28:53,600
But I really like it.
Please let me have it.

388
00:28:53,680 --> 00:28:54,720
No, sorry.

389
00:28:55,280 --> 00:28:58,200
Then I'll return it
to Mr. Singha for you, Auntie.

390
00:28:58,280 --> 00:28:59,600
Please give it to me.

391
00:29:00,400 --> 00:29:01,880
That's not a good idea.

392
00:29:01,960 --> 00:29:06,560
If you take it in carelessly
and Mr. Singha sees it,

393
00:29:06,640 --> 00:29:08,000
there'll be trouble.

394
00:29:08,080 --> 00:29:10,400
-I'll be going now.
-Auntie!

395
00:29:11,080 --> 00:29:12,920
-Auntie!
-Wait.

396
00:29:13,000 --> 00:29:15,800
Calm down. It's okay.

397
00:29:15,880 --> 00:29:17,160
There'll be another chance.

398
00:29:25,760 --> 00:29:26,960
Come on. It's okay.

399
00:29:27,560 --> 00:29:30,360
Aunt Riam, where are you taking that bear?

400
00:29:31,040 --> 00:29:32,280
I'm not taking it anywhere.

401
00:29:32,360 --> 00:29:35,040
It just fell outside.

402
00:29:36,480 --> 00:29:37,760
Fell outside?

403
00:29:38,720 --> 00:29:39,720
How's that possible?

404
00:29:39,800 --> 00:29:40,960
How did it end up outside?

405
00:29:41,480 --> 00:29:43,400
I honestly don't know.

406
00:29:44,200 --> 00:29:45,120
I think

407
00:29:45,200 --> 00:29:47,120
it probably fell over
during the earlier chaos.

408
00:29:47,880 --> 00:29:49,200
Puna ran to the balcony.

409
00:29:50,000 --> 00:29:53,160
That's where Aunt Riam

410
00:29:53,240 --> 00:29:55,640
usually puts pillows
and plushies to air out.

411
00:29:55,720 --> 00:29:57,240
It must've fallen then.

412
00:29:57,960 --> 00:29:58,840
That's right.

413
00:29:59,480 --> 00:30:03,040
Miss Puna even said
she really likes this bear

414
00:30:03,120 --> 00:30:04,640
and asked for it.

415
00:30:04,720 --> 00:30:08,120
But I didn't dare give it.
I told her you're very protective of it.

416
00:30:09,120 --> 00:30:11,840
Alright, enough talk. Just put it away.

417
00:30:18,840 --> 00:30:19,800
Dad.

418
00:30:22,920 --> 00:30:24,000
Are you alright?

419
00:30:27,000 --> 00:30:27,920
Nothing.

420
00:30:32,320 --> 00:30:35,160
Miss Praewa, you and Puna
already know each other?

421
00:30:35,880 --> 00:30:36,760
Yes, that's right.

422
00:30:37,560 --> 00:30:40,000
It's because something happened.

423
00:30:40,080 --> 00:30:41,200
Where do you think you're going?

424
00:30:41,280 --> 00:30:42,400
Give it here.

425
00:30:45,680 --> 00:30:47,000
Let's go! Run!

426
00:30:47,600 --> 00:30:51,320
And Puna helped me out,
so we got to know each other.

427
00:30:52,040 --> 00:30:54,880
-Thanks again, Puna.
-No problem.

428
00:30:54,960 --> 00:30:58,600
Since the boss isn't around today,
you can talk to me about anything.

429
00:30:58,680 --> 00:31:00,160
I'll bring it up later.

430
00:31:02,440 --> 00:31:04,080
The thing is,

431
00:31:04,160 --> 00:31:06,080
the show <i>Top Country Hits</i>

432
00:31:06,160 --> 00:31:07,600
is planning a charity concert.

433
00:31:08,440 --> 00:31:11,480
I suggested to the company
that Puna perform.

434
00:31:12,360 --> 00:31:16,200
It's a big event,
and it'll be streamed live on our page.

435
00:31:18,040 --> 00:31:19,360
That's a great honor

436
00:31:19,440 --> 00:31:21,800
that you're showing interest
in a new artist like Puna.

437
00:31:21,880 --> 00:31:25,280
If she gets a spot,
it'll be her very first concert.

438
00:31:26,840 --> 00:31:29,720
So, what time would I perform
at the concert?

439
00:31:29,800 --> 00:31:32,120
There's an extra slot at midnight.

440
00:31:32,760 --> 00:31:34,320
But we'll need to confirm it.

441
00:31:34,400 --> 00:31:35,840
Miss Prae.

442
00:31:36,400 --> 00:31:38,240
If Puna's slot is at midnight,

443
00:31:38,320 --> 00:31:40,480
I don't think the boss will approve.

444
00:31:40,560 --> 00:31:42,120
That's too late.

445
00:31:42,200 --> 00:31:45,080
What time do Maria and Sonrak
have their slots?

446
00:31:47,680 --> 00:31:48,520
Seven p.m.

447
00:31:50,600 --> 00:31:52,640
Can I have the slot before seven,

448
00:31:52,720 --> 00:31:54,720
so Puna performs before them?

449
00:31:56,560 --> 00:31:58,960
Yes. If it's prime time,

450
00:31:59,040 --> 00:32:01,120
I'm sure the boss will be fine with it.

451
00:32:02,920 --> 00:32:05,560
I'll note it for now

452
00:32:05,640 --> 00:32:08,760
and rearrange the schedule.

453
00:32:10,120 --> 00:32:12,160
For someone as sweet as Puna,

454
00:32:12,240 --> 00:32:13,760
I'll do my best.

455
00:32:14,640 --> 00:32:15,640
Thank you.

456
00:32:30,960 --> 00:32:33,160
Kamnan, Miss Ice is here.

457
00:32:33,240 --> 00:32:34,640
-Let her in.
-Yes.

458
00:32:37,320 --> 00:32:40,200
Come here, dear.

459
00:32:40,280 --> 00:32:41,880
Alright, have a seat.

460
00:32:44,760 --> 00:32:47,240
You called me, Uncle. What's up?

461
00:32:47,320 --> 00:32:51,480
You know why I sent you
to Darathong Music, right?

462
00:32:51,560 --> 00:32:54,640
You sent me sent me to monitor things

463
00:32:54,720 --> 00:32:57,560
and report on matters
at the company on your behalf.

464
00:32:58,160 --> 00:33:00,840
And the accounts that Singha sent to me,

465
00:33:02,640 --> 00:33:04,600
do you know what's wrong with them?

466
00:33:04,680 --> 00:33:05,800
Yes, I know.

467
00:33:05,880 --> 00:33:10,160
Singha had the accounting department
make two sets of these books.

468
00:33:10,240 --> 00:33:11,920
One is the real version,

469
00:33:12,000 --> 00:33:14,000
and the other is a doctored copy,

470
00:33:14,080 --> 00:33:15,520
sent to you to put you at ease.

471
00:33:15,600 --> 00:33:19,040
And the budget I approved

472
00:33:19,120 --> 00:33:20,360
for the artist Puna,

473
00:33:21,520 --> 00:33:22,880
you already know about that?

474
00:33:22,960 --> 00:33:24,240
Yes.

475
00:33:24,320 --> 00:33:27,720
As for Puna's budget, Singha diverted it

476
00:33:27,800 --> 00:33:29,360
to another business,

477
00:33:29,440 --> 00:33:31,160
which has nothing to do with our company.

478
00:33:33,120 --> 00:33:34,240
What kind of business?

479
00:33:38,160 --> 00:33:39,520
Tell me.

480
00:33:40,920 --> 00:33:42,800
I don't have solid proof.

481
00:33:42,880 --> 00:33:45,440
But from what I overheard,

482
00:33:45,520 --> 00:33:47,080
I guess…

483
00:33:49,680 --> 00:33:51,760
What did he use my money for?

484
00:33:54,640 --> 00:33:56,160
Probably for drugs.

485
00:33:58,640 --> 00:33:59,640
Drugs?

486
00:34:13,560 --> 00:34:14,639
Hello, Kamnan.

487
00:34:14,719 --> 00:34:16,800
May I take a moment of your time?

488
00:34:17,560 --> 00:34:20,440
How's the investigation
I sent you on going?

489
00:34:20,520 --> 00:34:23,080
I heard there's a delivery
scheduled tonight.

490
00:34:24,320 --> 00:34:25,800
But isn't there a concert tonight?

491
00:34:26,400 --> 00:34:30,360
Yes, they like to use the chaos
as cover to make their deliveries.

492
00:34:31,199 --> 00:34:33,840
I want to catch them red-handed.

493
00:34:35,199 --> 00:34:38,440
Understood. I've already coordinated
with central police.

494
00:34:38,520 --> 00:34:40,639
Tonight, we'll catch them for sure.

495
00:34:48,159 --> 00:34:51,120
DARATHONG MUSIC

496
00:34:51,719 --> 00:34:54,719
Singha, tonight General Jiang
has arranged to pick up the goods.

497
00:34:55,320 --> 00:34:56,400
Okay.

498
00:34:56,480 --> 00:34:57,920
Are they ready?

499
00:34:58,000 --> 00:34:59,320
Packed and ready.

500
00:35:00,160 --> 00:35:02,680
But we still can't find
a transport vehicle.

501
00:35:03,960 --> 00:35:04,960
Why not?

502
00:35:06,720 --> 00:35:09,400
Sergeant Biew reported that lately,

503
00:35:09,480 --> 00:35:11,280
Captain Tom

504
00:35:11,360 --> 00:35:13,320
has secretly been contacting
central police

505
00:35:13,960 --> 00:35:15,840
without informing the superintendent.

506
00:35:15,920 --> 00:35:17,680
I'm worried

507
00:35:18,280 --> 00:35:19,560
he might figure us out.

508
00:35:23,880 --> 00:35:24,760
No transport.

509
00:35:29,000 --> 00:35:30,360
Maybe we can use the artist's car?

510
00:35:31,920 --> 00:35:33,200
There's a concert tonight.

511
00:35:34,760 --> 00:35:37,640
Seriously? Sonrak's car?

512
00:35:41,160 --> 00:35:42,720
We have no choice.

513
00:35:46,000 --> 00:35:47,760
But you must handle it carefully.

514
00:35:48,400 --> 00:35:50,000
Don't let Sonrak get into trouble.

515
00:35:50,880 --> 00:35:51,960
Got it.

516
00:35:53,000 --> 00:35:54,680
I promise I'll take good care of it.

517
00:36:07,840 --> 00:36:09,640
One more hour before we leave.

518
00:36:10,240 --> 00:36:11,800
We have to be on stage at 7 p.m. sharp.

519
00:36:12,560 --> 00:36:15,200
This show is serious about timing.
We can't be late.

520
00:36:17,400 --> 00:36:18,600
We perform together, right?

521
00:36:19,200 --> 00:36:21,360
Yes, the producers
want you to go on together.

522
00:36:21,440 --> 00:36:23,640
Who's handling the outfits?

523
00:36:24,280 --> 00:36:25,120
That's me.

524
00:36:25,200 --> 00:36:26,960
I've taken care of everything.

525
00:36:28,760 --> 00:36:30,800
Last time, there was a tear.

526
00:36:32,080 --> 00:36:33,240
Has it been fixed?

527
00:36:33,840 --> 00:36:36,160
Hey, don't worry.

528
00:36:36,240 --> 00:36:37,320
Sophie's a professional.

529
00:36:38,480 --> 00:36:40,160
Do you know my level?

530
00:36:40,240 --> 00:36:41,960
I've handled a lot of events already.

531
00:37:07,840 --> 00:37:11,040
Hey, what are those boxes?
They're not on the list.

532
00:37:16,800 --> 00:37:18,480
Take these two boxes to the concert.

533
00:37:20,440 --> 00:37:21,880
Mr. Sonrak didn't mention them at all.

534
00:37:22,600 --> 00:37:23,880
It wasn't Mr. Sonrak.

535
00:37:24,520 --> 00:37:27,160
Mr. Singha ordered it. They're props.

536
00:37:27,800 --> 00:37:29,000
Just leave them in the car.

537
00:37:29,720 --> 00:37:30,920
Don't touch them.

538
00:37:41,520 --> 00:37:42,640
You heard that?

539
00:37:43,760 --> 00:37:44,640
Yeah.

540
00:37:45,640 --> 00:37:46,640
Let me take a look.

541
00:37:47,520 --> 00:37:48,760
Keep watch around here for me.

542
00:38:25,640 --> 00:38:26,880
How's it?

543
00:38:27,920 --> 00:38:28,960
It's the stuff.

544
00:38:29,040 --> 00:38:30,920
-Drugs?
-Yeah.

545
00:38:32,360 --> 00:38:34,120
So what now?

546
00:38:36,680 --> 00:38:39,560
You just play along for now.
I'll handle it.

547
00:38:41,720 --> 00:38:43,840
Put them back in the car. No slacking.

548
00:39:05,480 --> 00:39:07,360
SAVAGE TIGER

549
00:39:26,760 --> 00:39:27,880
Hello.

550
00:39:29,000 --> 00:39:30,040
Hello.

551
00:39:31,760 --> 00:39:32,800
Hello.

552
00:39:32,880 --> 00:39:35,520
If you have any information,
you can report it to me.

553
00:39:36,600 --> 00:39:38,240
Are you still there?

554
00:39:40,080 --> 00:39:42,120
Sergeant, that's my phone.

555
00:39:42,200 --> 00:39:45,840
Well, I just answered it for you.

556
00:39:47,680 --> 00:39:48,600
Take it back.

557
00:39:50,400 --> 00:39:52,840
Captain Tom speaking. Who's that?

558
00:39:54,520 --> 00:39:56,280
Yes. Sure.

559
00:39:56,360 --> 00:39:58,480
Yes, that's good.

560
00:39:58,560 --> 00:40:02,040
We'll wear this on stage.

561
00:40:02,120 --> 00:40:04,560
-It catches the light beautifully.
-Okay.

562
00:40:05,440 --> 00:40:07,920
Didn't I have this shirt sent for repair?

563
00:40:08,000 --> 00:40:09,080
Why is it still ripped?

564
00:40:09,160 --> 00:40:10,280
Huh?

565
00:40:11,120 --> 00:40:13,400
Hey, Sophie.

566
00:40:13,480 --> 00:40:14,840
Didn't you say it was sent for repair?

567
00:40:16,200 --> 00:40:18,720
It was fixed, but not this one.

568
00:40:18,800 --> 00:40:20,840
Huh, which one did you repair?

569
00:40:22,960 --> 00:40:25,240
This one was fixed. Mr. Sonrak.

570
00:40:25,320 --> 00:40:28,480
Can you wear this for now?
It really suits you.

571
00:40:28,560 --> 00:40:29,800
-It suits me?
-Yes.

572
00:40:29,880 --> 00:40:33,160
But this is a dancer's costume.
How can I wear it?

573
00:40:33,240 --> 00:40:34,080
Are you serious?

574
00:40:36,720 --> 00:40:38,760
How do you two even work?

575
00:40:38,840 --> 00:40:41,840
Sending the dancer's outfit to be fixed
but not the artist's costume.

576
00:40:42,880 --> 00:40:46,160
Hey, we went together
when we took them to be repaired.

577
00:40:47,360 --> 00:40:48,200
Yes.

578
00:40:48,280 --> 00:40:51,080
I went, but how was I supposed to know
which one needed fixing?

579
00:40:51,640 --> 00:40:54,640
You're the one in charge of the outfits.
How can you pin this on me?

580
00:40:55,560 --> 00:40:57,880
Hey, we went together.

581
00:40:57,960 --> 00:40:59,920
If anyone's at fault, it's all of us.

582
00:41:00,520 --> 00:41:02,760
Enough. Stop blaming each other already.

583
00:41:03,520 --> 00:41:05,640
You have no sense of responsibility.

584
00:41:05,720 --> 00:41:07,440
You make mistakes,
but won't own up to them.

585
00:41:08,160 --> 00:41:10,280
What's that? Leave already.
Get out of here.

586
00:41:11,560 --> 00:41:14,720
-But the outfit still isn't fixed
-Forget it. You can leave.

587
00:41:15,840 --> 00:41:16,960
Yes.

588
00:41:26,320 --> 00:41:28,080
What should we do now, Mr. Sonrak?

589
00:41:29,000 --> 00:41:29,920
Change into a new outfit?

590
00:41:30,000 --> 00:41:32,080
How could I change it?
This is the concept outfit.

591
00:41:33,680 --> 00:41:35,120
But it's almost time.

592
00:41:36,840 --> 00:41:38,880
I'll call my housekeeper.

593
00:41:38,960 --> 00:41:39,960
She's good at sewing.

594
00:41:46,000 --> 00:41:49,320
Hello, Auntie.
Please come to the office quickly.

595
00:41:49,960 --> 00:41:51,400
Well, my outfit got ripped.

596
00:41:52,320 --> 00:41:53,360
Come as fast as you can.

597
00:42:02,080 --> 00:42:04,240
Mine hasn't been ironed either.

598
00:42:04,320 --> 00:42:05,720
It's all wrinkled.

599
00:42:06,920 --> 00:42:09,440
Ever since Puna's not here,
everything's gone wrong.

600
00:42:30,400 --> 00:42:31,160
How's it going?

601
00:42:33,040 --> 00:42:34,120
All set.

602
00:42:40,760 --> 00:42:41,840
Hey.

603
00:42:42,360 --> 00:42:43,320
What time are you heading out?

604
00:42:44,560 --> 00:42:46,480
Mr. Sonrak hasn't come down yet.

605
00:42:55,120 --> 00:42:55,960
Hello.

606
00:42:59,680 --> 00:43:01,880
Okay. Got it.

607
00:43:01,960 --> 00:43:03,200
I'll go on ahead

608
00:43:07,440 --> 00:43:09,360
Go on ahead? Something wrong?

609
00:43:09,440 --> 00:43:11,600
Mr. Sonrak's outfit is ripped,
needs to be repaired.

610
00:43:12,280 --> 00:43:15,880
I have to take the props ahead
and prep for filming.

611
00:43:17,600 --> 00:43:19,360
Then hurry up and go already, Chaiya.

612
00:43:20,000 --> 00:43:21,040
We've got it covered here.

613
00:43:23,640 --> 00:43:24,880
Let's go.

614
00:43:47,040 --> 00:43:48,640
Always scolding.

615
00:43:48,720 --> 00:43:51,080
We work our butts off
and never get a single word of praise.

616
00:43:52,200 --> 00:43:55,840
Yeah, Miss Maria too!
Suddenly she starts picking on us.

617
00:43:55,920 --> 00:43:56,920
Is that right?

618
00:43:57,600 --> 00:43:58,560
It's not right at all!

619
00:43:59,920 --> 00:44:02,480
We're on the same team.
Instead of backing us up,

620
00:44:02,560 --> 00:44:04,800
she joins in and scolds with him.

621
00:44:05,600 --> 00:44:08,440
I'm so fed up. Don't want to work anymore.
So frustrating!

622
00:44:09,200 --> 00:44:11,440
It's okay. Calm down.

623
00:44:33,160 --> 00:44:36,440
-You look stunning, Puna!
-Absolutely beautiful!

624
00:44:36,520 --> 00:44:37,800
Thanks!

625
00:44:40,440 --> 00:44:43,480
It's your first concert. Give it your all.

626
00:44:43,560 --> 00:44:46,080
I heard Boss Nok

627
00:44:46,160 --> 00:44:48,360
is watching the live broadcast.

628
00:44:48,440 --> 00:44:52,200
Puna, you're going to crush it this time!

629
00:44:53,200 --> 00:44:55,280
Sathu!

630
00:44:55,360 --> 00:44:56,320
Bless me!

631
00:44:59,240 --> 00:45:00,720
I'm so excited!

632
00:45:03,240 --> 00:45:04,240
Are you ready, Puna?

633
00:45:04,320 --> 00:45:05,720
I'm totally ready!

634
00:45:05,800 --> 00:45:07,920
I'll come find you closer to showtime.

635
00:45:11,760 --> 00:45:15,840
By the way, Mr. Sonrak and Miss Maria
are still not here?

636
00:45:16,440 --> 00:45:19,080
Can you call the artists
from Darathong Music?

637
00:45:19,160 --> 00:45:20,320
Yes.

638
00:45:23,120 --> 00:45:24,360
Why aren't they here yet?

639
00:45:27,040 --> 00:45:28,400
You look amazing!

640
00:45:28,480 --> 00:45:29,640
Thank you.

641
00:45:39,000 --> 00:45:40,000
Almost done, Auntie?

642
00:45:41,360 --> 00:45:43,360
Just a bit more. It's almost finished.

643
00:45:43,440 --> 00:45:46,880
This shirt belongs to a sponsor,
so I have to sew it carefully.

644
00:45:46,960 --> 00:45:47,840
Got it.

645
00:45:51,880 --> 00:45:52,720
Need some help?

646
00:45:55,120 --> 00:45:57,200
No! I can handle it myself.

647
00:45:59,600 --> 00:46:02,280
What happened to your two assistants?

648
00:46:04,680 --> 00:46:06,720
Don't ask! It's frustrating!

649
00:46:10,120 --> 00:46:11,040
Mr. Sonrak.

650
00:46:11,800 --> 00:46:13,760
The concert team just called
asking for you.

651
00:46:15,360 --> 00:46:17,360
Didn't you see it's not ready yet?

652
00:46:18,080 --> 00:46:20,440
Tell them to wait a bit.

653
00:46:21,560 --> 00:46:22,640
Yes.

654
00:46:32,280 --> 00:46:34,880
Mr. Sonrak is on the way.
He said to wait a moment.

655
00:46:36,520 --> 00:46:37,880
How can we wait?

656
00:46:37,960 --> 00:46:41,560
I told them to be on standby.
It's almost showtime.

657
00:46:42,760 --> 00:46:43,880
This is ridiculous.

658
00:46:49,360 --> 00:46:50,480
Yes, Boss?

659
00:46:53,320 --> 00:46:54,480
What?

660
00:46:55,200 --> 00:46:56,200
The artist wants to cancel?

661
00:47:01,680 --> 00:47:02,600
Okay.

662
00:47:02,680 --> 00:47:05,400
I'll try to find a replacement.

663
00:47:07,280 --> 00:47:08,280
Yes.

664
00:47:09,160 --> 00:47:10,480
What happened, Ms. Prae?

665
00:47:11,680 --> 00:47:14,600
Miss Aomnoi Kloyjai requested to cancel.

666
00:47:14,680 --> 00:47:16,320
Her car had an accident.

667
00:47:16,880 --> 00:47:18,640
We need an emergency replacement.

668
00:47:18,720 --> 00:47:21,360
At the last minute like this,
who can we get?

669
00:47:27,160 --> 00:47:28,920
Alright, I'll handle it.

670
00:47:29,000 --> 00:47:30,320
Yes, Ms. Praewa.

671
00:47:39,840 --> 00:47:42,760
Hey, Chaiya! Nobody else with you?

672
00:47:42,840 --> 00:47:45,760
I'm here. Didn't you see, Teacher?

673
00:47:45,840 --> 00:47:48,560
I meant Sonrak and Maria!

674
00:47:48,640 --> 00:47:50,800
I was sent ahead, Teacher.

675
00:47:52,480 --> 00:47:53,320
Puna.

676
00:47:54,280 --> 00:47:56,880
Today I'll be cheering for you
from the front of the stage.

677
00:48:00,880 --> 00:48:02,880
Can you record a clip for me?

678
00:48:02,960 --> 00:48:04,600
I want to see any mistakes I make.

679
00:48:04,680 --> 00:48:05,880
Sure.

680
00:48:11,880 --> 00:48:12,880
She's from another label.

681
00:48:14,600 --> 00:48:15,480
How could you film her?

682
00:48:19,840 --> 00:48:23,160
You don't need to film.
I'll let the teacher handle it.

683
00:48:39,800 --> 00:48:42,080
Mr. Chaiya, are you here to shoot content?

684
00:48:42,920 --> 00:48:43,840
Yes.

685
00:48:45,000 --> 00:48:47,680
Please wait for Mr. Sonrak and Maria.
They should be here soon.

686
00:48:49,920 --> 00:48:53,120
Right now, the artist schedule
is all messed up.

687
00:48:53,200 --> 00:48:54,640
One of the singers canceled.

688
00:48:54,720 --> 00:48:57,880
If Miss Maria and Mr. Sonrak are late,
the whole event could fall apart.

689
00:48:59,760 --> 00:49:02,960
Teacher, is it him,

690
00:49:03,040 --> 00:49:06,040
the one whose voice
is used as your ringtone?

691
00:49:06,120 --> 00:49:08,360
Yes, nice voice, isn't it?

692
00:49:08,440 --> 00:49:09,880
He has such a great voice!

693
00:49:10,480 --> 00:49:12,400
He could be a singer.

694
00:49:12,480 --> 00:49:14,360
You're exaggerating.

695
00:49:15,040 --> 00:49:16,280
It's not that great.

696
00:49:18,760 --> 00:49:20,360
You can sing too, Mr. Chaiya?

697
00:49:26,200 --> 00:49:27,200
What chance are you talking about?

698
00:49:27,280 --> 00:49:29,080
NEXT EPISODE

699
00:49:29,160 --> 00:49:31,360
The chance for us

700
00:49:32,160 --> 00:49:33,560
to get to know each other like before.

701
00:49:33,640 --> 00:49:35,360
Do I really have that much buzz?

702
00:49:35,440 --> 00:49:37,280
If you want to know how much,

703
00:49:37,360 --> 00:49:38,640
let's go give an interview.

704
00:49:40,040 --> 00:49:42,040
I'll be watching

705
00:49:43,120 --> 00:49:45,440
to see how far your talent

706
00:49:46,440 --> 00:49:48,520
can really go.

707
00:49:48,600 --> 00:49:49,600
What are you doing?

708
00:52:20,160 --> 00:52:22,320
Subtitle translation by:
Chomchanach Yanaharn
